   <concept id="FAR_19_1406">
      <title>
         <ph props="autonumber">19.1406</ph>
         <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 January 30, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2022-009?>Sole source awards.<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 19.1406 by—   a.  Revising the section heading; ?></ph>
      </title>
      <conbody>
         <ol id="d1245e13">
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(a)</ph>
                  
						             A contracting officer shall consider a contract award to a SDVOSB concern on a sole source basis (see <xref href="6.302-5.dita#FAR_6_302_5"
                        base="i1119624"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">6.302-5</xref>(b)(6)), before considering small business set-asides (see <xref href="19.203.dita#FAR_19_203"
                        base="i1101696"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">19.203</xref> and subpart <xref href="Subpart_19.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_5"
                        base="i1100723"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">19.5</xref>) provided none of the exclusions of <xref href="19.1404.dita#FAR_19_1404"
                        base="i1099419"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">19.1404</xref> apply and—</p>
               <ol id="d1245e35">
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e28">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(1)</ph>
                        
								                 The contracting officer does not have a reasonable expectation that offers would be received from two or more service-disabled veteran-owned small business concerns;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e33">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(2)</ph>
                        
								                 The anticipated award price of the contract, including options, will not exceed-</p>
                     <ol id="d1245e54">
                        <li>
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e39">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(i)</ph>
                              
										                    
										
											$7 million
										 for a requirement within the NAICS codes for manufacturing; or</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e44">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(ii)</ph>
                              
										                     $4 million for a requirement within any other NAICS code;</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e49">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(3)</ph>
                        
								                 The requirement is not currently being performed by an 8(a) participant under the provisions of <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart">subpart  19.8</xref> or has been accepted as a requirement by SBA under <xref href="Subpart_19.8.dita#FAR_Subpart_19_8"
                              base="i1099848"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart">subpart  19.8</xref>;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e60">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(4)</ph>
                        
								                 The service-disabled veteran-owned small business concern has been determined to be a responsible contractor with respect to performance; and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e65">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(5)</ph>
                        
								                 Award can be made at a fair and reasonable price.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e73">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 January 30, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber]  FAR Case 2022-009?>Effective January 1, 2024, a contracting officer shall only award a sole-source contract to a concern that—<?FM MARKER [Why] b.  Redesignating paragraph (b) as paragraph (c), and adding a new paragraph (b); and?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e82">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(1)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 January 30, 2024">Is designated in SAM as an SDVOSB concern certified by SBA; or</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d1282e88">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(2)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 January 30, 2024">Has represented that it is an SDVOSB concern in SAM and submitted an application for certification to SBA on or before December 31, 2023. Pending applications for certification are in the SBA Veteran Small Business Certification Program database at <xref href="https://veterans.certify.sba.gov"
                                 format="html"
                                 scope="external">https://veterans.certify.sba.gov</xref>.</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d1279e70">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph " platform="hide">(c)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2024-03 January 30, 2024"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber]  FAR Case 2022-009?>The SBA has the right to appeal the contracting officer’s decision not to make an SDVOSB sole-source award.<?FM MARKER [Why] c.  Revising the newly redesignated paragraph (c).?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
